.TH SCHUPFN 1 "2026-04-30" "schupfn 0.2.0"
.SH NAME
schupfn \- run toolbox containers in virtual machines
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B schupfn create
.RI [ name ]
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B schupfn enter
.RI [ name ]
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B schupfn start
.RI [ name ]
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B schupfn stop
.RI [ name ]
.br
.B schupfn join
.RI [ name ]
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B schupfn list
.br
.B schupfn clean
.RI [ name ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B schupfn
boots a toolbox container as a virtual machine using
.BR qemu (1).
The container is converted to a qcow2 disk image and booted with the
host kernel.
The current working directory is mounted read\-write inside the VM at
the same path; everything else on the host is inaccessible.
.PP
The intended use is sandboxing: the VM boundary provides stronger
isolation than a container, which matters when running untrusted code
or AI agents that might try to break out of their sandbox.
.PP
The workflow is:
.IP 1. 4
Create and configure a toolbox container the usual way
.RI ( "toolbox create" ,
.IR "toolbox run" ).
.IP 2.
Run
.B schupfn create
to export the container's filesystem to a qcow2 disk image.
.IP 3.
Run
.B schupfn enter
to boot the image as a VM with the host kernel and SSH in.
.IP 4.
Work inside the VM as you would inside
.BR toolbox (1).
When you exit, the VM shuts down.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS create \fR[\fIname\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
Export the toolbox container
.I name
to a qcow2 disk image.
The image is cached and reused by
.B schupfn enter
until the container changes.
If
.I name
is omitted, the
.B container
field from the configuration file is used (see
.BR "CONFIGURATION FILE" ).
.PP
The packages
.BR openssh\-server ,
.BR systemd\-udev ,
and
.BR dbus\-broker
are required and installed automatically during image creation.
.PP
If the image already exists, the command exits with an error unless
.B \-\-force
is given.
.PP
The options are as follows:
.TP
.B \-\-force
Rebuild the image even if one already exists.
.TP
.BI \-\-image\-size " size"
Size of the qcow2 disk image, e.g.\&
.BR 4G ,
.BR 10G .
If not specified, the image is auto\-sized from the container
(tarball size + 50% headroom, minimum 2G).
.TP
.BI \-\-install\-packages " pkg"
Install additional packages in the image via
.BR dnf (8).
This option may be given multiple times.
Packages are installed before the image is finalized, so they are
available immediately when the VM boots. Typically all required packages
should be in the toolbox container, this option should only
be used for packages that are required in the VM but are not supposed
to be in the toolbox.
.TP
.BI \-\-config " path"
Load the configuration file from
.I path
instead of searching for
.B .schupfn/config.yml
in parent directories.
It is an error if the file does not exist.
.SS enter \fR[\fIname\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
Boot a previously created VM image and connect to it via SSH.
The image must already exist; run
.B schupfn create
first to export the container to a disk image.
If
.I name
is omitted, the
.B container
field from the configuration file is used (see
.BR "CONFIGURATION FILE" ).
.PP
The options are as follows:
.TP
.BI \-\-export\-ro " path"
Make an additional host path available in the VM.
If
.I path
is a directory (or a symlink to one), it is mounted read\-only at
its original absolute path via 9p.
If
.I path
is a file (or a symlink to one), it is copied into the VM at its
original absolute path (directory structure is preserved).
This option may be given multiple times.
.TP
.BI \-\-export\-rw " path"
Like
.B \-\-export\-ro
but directories are mounted read\-write.
This option may be given multiple times.
.TP
.BI \-\-export\-cow " path"
Like
.B \-\-export\-ro
but the directory is writable inside the VM via overlayfs.
Reads come from the host directory; writes go to a tmpfs upper layer
and are lost when the VM shuts down.
The host directory is never modified.
Only directories are supported (not individual files).
This option may be given multiple times.
.TP
.BI \-\-command " cmd"
Run
.I cmd
in the VM instead of starting an interactive shell.
The exit code of
.I cmd
is propagated as the exit code of
.BR schupfn .
.TP
.BI \-\-config " path"
Load the configuration file from
.I path
instead of searching for
.B .schupfn/config.yml
in parent directories.
It is an error if the file does not exist.
.TP
.BI \-\-memory " size"
Amount of memory for the VM, e.g.\&
.BR 4G ,
.BR 512M .
The default is
.BR 4G .
.TP
.BI \-\-cpus " n"
Number of CPUs for the VM.
Defaults to the host CPU count.
.TP
.B \-\-follow\-git\-worktrees
If the current directory is a git worktree, automatically export the
main git directory read\-write so that git operations work correctly
inside the VM.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-network
Disable the extra user\-mode network device.
The internal SSH network device is unaffected.
.TP
.BI \-\-display " type"
Add a display adapter to the VM.
.I type
is the qemu VGA model, e.g.\&
.BR virtio ,
.BR qxl ,
or
.BR std .
This is needed to run Xorg or Wayland compositors inside the VM.
Without this flag, the VM has no display adapter.
.TP
.B \-\-console
Boot with the serial console on stdio instead of connecting via SSH.
Useful for debugging boot issues.
Use Ctrl\-A X to quit the VM.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Show VM boot output on stderr.
.SS start \fR[\fIname\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
Start a VM in the background from a previously created image.
The VM keeps running until explicitly stopped with
.BR "schupfn stop" .
Use
.B schupfn join
to connect to the running VM.
.PP
The image must already exist; run
.B schupfn create
first.
If
.I name
is omitted, the
.B container
field from the configuration file is used.
.PP
The options are the same as for
.B enter
except that
.B \-\-command
and
.B \-\-console
are not available.
.SS stop \fR[\fIname\fR]
Shut down a running VM that was started with
.BR "schupfn start" .
If
.I name
is omitted and exactly one VM is running, that VM is stopped
automatically.
If multiple VMs are running, an interactive menu is presented.
.PP
If there are active
.B join
sessions, the command waits for them to disconnect before
shutting down the VM.
.SS join \fR[\fIname\fR] [\fIoptions\fR]
Open a new SSH session to an already\-running VM.
This allows multiple terminal sessions to share the same VM
without starting a second one.
.PP
If
.I name
is omitted and exactly one VM is running, that VM is joined
automatically.
If multiple VMs are running, an interactive menu is presented.
.PP
Session state is tracked in
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/schupfn/sessions/
and cleaned up automatically when the VM exits or when stale
sessions are detected.
.PP
Each active join session is tracked automatically.
When the
.B enter
session exits, the VM waits for all join sessions to disconnect
before shutting down.
.PP
The options are as follows:
.TP
.BI \-\-command " cmd"
Run
.I cmd
in the VM instead of starting an interactive shell.
The exit code of
.I cmd
is propagated as the exit code of
.BR schupfn .
.SS list
Show cached VM images with their status, number of
running VMs, size, and export date.
Images whose source container no longer exists are marked
.BR orphaned .
.SS clean \fR[\fIname\fR]
Remove cached VM images.
If
.I name
is given, only that entry is removed.
Otherwise all entries are removed after confirmation.
.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
.B schupfn
searches from
.B $PWD
upward for a file named
.BR .schupfn/config.yml .
The first one found is loaded.
If no local config file is found,
.B schupfn
falls back to
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/ :
first
.IR <container>\-config.yml
(if the container name is known from the command line), then
.IR default\-config.yml .
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
defaults to
.IR ~/.config
if unset.
.PP
Requires
.BR yq (1)
to be installed; if no configuration file is found,
.B yq
is not needed.
.PP
CLI arguments always take precedence over configuration file values.
For
.B \-\-export\-ro
and
.BR \-\-export\-rw ,
the configuration file list and CLI list are merged (config entries
first).
.PP
The following keys are recognised:
.TP
.B container
.RI ( string )
Default container name, used when none is given on the command line.
.TP
.B command
.RI ( string )
Command to run in the VM instead of an interactive shell.
Same as
.BR \-\-command .
.TP
.B export\-ro
.RI ( "list of paths" )
Paths to export read\-only into the VM.
Same as
.BR \-\-export\-ro .
.TP
.B export\-rw
.RI ( "list of paths" )
Paths to export read\-write into the VM.
Same as
.BR \-\-export\-rw .
.TP
.B export\-cow
.RI ( "list of paths" )
Paths to export with copy\-on\-write overlay.
Same as
.BR \-\-export\-cow .
.TP
.B follow\-git\-worktrees
.RI ( bool )
Automatically export the main git directory when working in a git worktree.
Same as
.BR \-\-follow\-git\-worktrees .
.TP
.B image.size
.RI ( string )
Size of the qcow2 disk image, e.g.\&
.BR 4G ,
.BR 10G .
Same as
.BR \-\-image\-size .
.TP
.B image.install\-packages
.RI ( "list of strings" )
Packages to install in the image via
.BR dnf (8).
Same as
.BR \-\-install\-packages .
.TP
.B vm.memory
.RI ( string )
VM memory.
Same as
.BR \-\-memory .
.TP
.B vm.cpus
.RI ( int )
VM CPU count.
Same as
.BR \-\-cpus .
.TP
.B vm.network
.RI ( bool )
Set to
.B false
to disable the extra network device.
Same as
.BR \-\-no\-network .
.TP
.B vm.display
.RI ( string )
Display adapter model (e.g.\&
.BR virtio ,
.BR qxl ,
.BR std ).
Same as
.BR \-\-display .
.SS Example
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
container: my\-toolbox
command: make test

export\-ro:
  \- ~/src/shared\-lib
  \- ~/.zshrc

export\-rw:
  \- ~/src/work\-in\-progress

vm:
  memory: 8G
  cpus: 4
  network: false
.EE
.in
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for user\-level configuration files.
Defaults to
.IR ~/.config .
When no local
.I .schupfn/config.yml
is found,
.B schupfn
looks for
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/<container>\-config.yml ,
then
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/default\-config.yml .
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Base directory for cached VM images.
Defaults to
.IR ~/.cache .
The cache lives under
.IR $XDG_CACHE_HOME/schupfn/images/ .
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Base directory for runtime session files.
Session files are stored in
.IR $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/schupfn/sessions/ .
When this variable is not set, session tracking is disabled
and the
.B join
command will not work.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .schupfn/config.yml
Per\-project configuration file, searched from
.B $PWD
upward.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/<container>\-config.yml
Container\-specific user\-level configuration file, used when no local
.I .schupfn/config.yml
is found and the container name is known from the command line.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/schupfn/default\-config.yml
User\-level default configuration file, used when no local
.I .schupfn/config.yml
or container\-specific config is found.
Defaults to
.IR ~/.config/schupfn/default\-config.yml .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/schupfn/images/<name>/
Cached qcow2 disk image and metadata for a container.
Managed by
.B schupfn list
and
.BR "schupfn clean" .
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/schupfn/sessions/
Runtime session files for active VMs.
Each file records the SSH port, PID, and working directory of a
running VM.
Used by
.B schupfn join
to connect to existing VMs.
Cleaned up automatically when VMs exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
In interactive mode (no
.BR \-\-command ),
.B schupfn
exits 0 on success.
Non\-zero SSH exit codes produce a warning but
.B schupfn
still exits 0.
.PP
With
.BR \-\-command ,
the exit code of the remote command is forwarded as the exit code of
.BR schupfn .
.SH EXAMPLES
Create a VM image from a toolbox container:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn create mybox
.EE
.in
.PP
Enter the VM:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn enter mybox
.EE
.in
.PP
Mount extra directories and copy dotfiles:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn enter mybox \-\-export\-ro ~/src/lib \-\-export\-ro ~/.vimrc
.EE
.in
.PP
Run a single command and exit:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn enter mybox \-\-command "make -j$(nproc) test"
.EE
.in
.PP
Start a VM in the background and connect later:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn start mybox
schupfn join mybox
schupfn stop mybox
.EE
.in
.PP
Join a running VM from another terminal:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn join mybox
.EE
.in
.PP
Join the only running VM (name auto\-detected):
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn join
.EE
.in
.PP
Run a command in a running VM without an interactive shell:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn join mybox \-\-command "make test"
.EE
.in
.PP
Use a config file so you only need to type:
.PP
.in +4n
.EX
schupfn create
schupfn enter
.EE
.in
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR toolbox (1),
.BR podman (1),
.BR qemu\-system\-x86_64 (1),
.BR virt\-make\-fs (1),
.BR virt\-customize (1),
.BR ssh (1),
.BR yq (1)
